  "market_context": "NQ trading within a daily range in April 2024 with prior swing highs and lows visible. Analyst is reviewing recent daily candles to identify where liquidity has been swept versus where failure swings remain untouched, building a directional bias from those liquidity signatures.",
  "key_observation": "When the lows of the range get swept and close back inside (creating high resistance liquidity) while the highs remain as untaken failure swings, the configuration favors a long bias targeting the failure swing highs as draw on liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the daily range on NQ by locating the recent swing high and swing low.",
    "Observe that the first attempt sweeps a high while leaving a failure swing — note that ideally the high should not be taken before the low runs.",
    "Advance price one day and see the low get swept with a closure back inside the range, establishing high resistance liquidity on the lows.",
    "Confirm the highs are still failure swings that have not been protected, marking them as low resistance draw on liquidity.",
    "Combine high resistance liquidity on the lows with failure swings on the highs to bias for long setups targeting the highs.",
    "Let the scenario play out and observe price running the high, validating the bias."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price ran the high after the low was swept and closed back inside the range, validating the long bias.",
  "lessons": "Mapping where high resistance liquidity sits versus where failure swings remain on the daily chart provides a clean directional bias: trade away from high resistance liquidity toward unprotected failure swings.",
